			<p><strong>Your Dream Website</strong><br> 
			  <br>
		    Create and publish your dream website using all the techniques you'ave learned from this course including the following:</p>
			<p>*basic xhtml template<br>
			  *incorporate the following tags - p(with the align attribute), div, h1-h6, br, hr, meta <br>
			  *DON&rsquo;T FORGET THE TITLE!<br>
			  *include background color(hex code only!) <br>
			  *include at least three different font colors(hex codes only!) and two different font styles <br>
			  *include at least your name in xhtml comments<br>
			*include CSS style sheet<br>
			  *create a directory on your Pitt unix account in the &quot;public/html&quot; directories called &quot;cs134&quot; <br>
			  *publish the site called &quot;hw1.html&quot; to your &quot;cs134&quot; directory and email me (<a href="mailto:chang@cs.pitt.edu">chang@cs.pitt.edu</a>) the URL.  Please put &quot;CS134 HW&quot; in subject line <br>
			  *present your website in class </p>

<h3>You should design and create your own unique dream website.
Extensively copying someone else's website, if discovered by the
instructor, would result in a ZERO for the homework!</h3>
<hr>
The following are the guidelines for grading your homework:

<br>(2 pts) website is published in cs134 directory and easily accessible (2 pts) or published on your own PC (1 pt)
  (you will receive 0 point otherwise)
<br>(2 pts) utilize most of the basic techniques such as xhtml template, 
p, div, h1-h6, br, hr, meta, title, background color, at least three
different font colors and two font sizes, name in xhtml comments (2 pts) or only some of the above (1 pt)
<br>(2 pts) demo how to use CSS style sheets
to change entire website (2 pts) or at least include style sheets (1 pt)
<br>(2 pts) use table, division or frame for formatting the page with flexibility (2 pts) or without flexibility (1 pt)
<br>(2 pts) include Javascript to do something creative (2 pts) or at least something useful for your website (1 pt)
  (Javascript must contribute to the functionalities of your website)
<br>(2 pts) content is entirely original (2 pts) or based upon author's experience (1 pt)
<br>(2 pts) content includes 8+ pages (2 pts) or 4+ pages (1 pt)
<br>(2 pts) content is rich in media variety (2 pts) or has some media variety (1 pt)
  (use of animation, video clips, multimedia would help)
<br>(2 pts) content is colorful, elegant and pleasing (2 pts) or somewhat colorful (1 pt)
<br>(2 pts) content is mobile with 'm' version (2 pts) or somewhat mobile with responsive (relative) design (1 pt)

<p>
Total 20 points:  (2)publish (2)basic (2) style (2)format (2)Java (2)orig (2)size (2)rich (2)color (2)mobile
<p>
Doe,John,  ( )publish ( )basic ( ) style ( )format ( )Java ( )orig ( )size ( )rich ( )color ( )mobile [  ]Total

<p>
To understand how your homework is graded,
notice after the homework grade there are some letters,
for example:   "17 ocm".
The letters individually have the following meanings:
<pre>
    p  published
    b  basic techniques
    t  style sheet
    f  format
    j  javascript
    o  originality
    s  size
    r  richness
    c  color
    m  mobile
</pre>

If you see lower-case letters, it means a deduction 
of 1 point in that category.
If you see upper-case letters, it means a deduction
of 2 points in that category.

Therefore, "17 ocm" means the homework earns 17 points, with deduction of 1 point each
in the three categories of originality, color and
mobile accessibility.

<p><b>
Unlike the previous lab exercises, for this exercise
very few students will earn perfect score. </b>
